		<div class="post" id="post-3834890">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3834890)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3834890">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nederbird" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2854162); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2854162&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182118" alt="Nederbird" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2854162)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nederbird" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2854162); return false;" >Nederbird</a></span> <span class="odate time_1528932549 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jun 2018 23:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3834890">
									

<p>I love the detail that went into researching the background and writing the descrption and reconnaissance. I leays appreciate good research.</p>
<p>I really do not like the very Hollywood-esque narrative style of the reports and testimonies, however. They seem very much to follow the the pattern of &quot;awesome fights with magic doomsday Nazis&quot; formula that's so emblematic of American comic books and cinema. Which, quite frankly, I feel only serves to dumb them down into cartoonish villains. The embellishments of the overly detailed fights strikes me as unprofessional, and the reckless flinging and destruction of the artifacts and magical items, which the Obskurakorps likely spent years no small fortune acquiring, just seems plain stupid. It's like teying to keep your enemy at bay by throwing ammunition at them.</p>
<p>Sorry if I'm harsh, but I've heard quite a few things about how clichéed Obskura articles are, and now that I've finally seen it, I'm&#8230; I dunno, disheartened? Is that the right word?</p>
<p>As such, I feel I will have to give this a -1, in spite of all the good effort that went into writing this. I'm sorry.</p>

							</div>

								
					
