				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2026083&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182118" alt="Dr_Grom" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2026083)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;" >Dr_Grom</a></span> <span class="odate time_1531316296 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Jul 2018 13:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3870116">
									

<p>First things first, corps is written Korps in German so unless &quot;Obskuracorps&quot; is a translation it should be written &quot;Obskurakorps&quot;. Not to mention that the term does not sound like anything the SS would come up with and a korps is a military unit the size of 3 divisions, although the term was not used in the Wehrmacht as far as I know.</p>
<p>I agree with Nederbörd, despite the setting it has little to do with Nazis, it's more like comic-good-magicians vs. comic-villain-magicians, and magic energy summed up to an equivalent of a modern medium sized nuke. The ease with witch all of them use their powers feels odd to me. They all seem way too powerfull.</p>
<p>I came here and read this series of articles to see if the OK is compatible with the SKP, a Nazi GOI of the German branch. It is not apparently. Furthermore it seems the OK is exactly what I wanted to prevent when I created the SKP hastingly shortly after the german branch was founded. As mentioned by others in the discussion of the Black Rope tale, hollywood Nazis contradict what we find appropriate use of the Nazi topic.</p>
<p>However I do not want to badmouth your article, it is well written and the format fits the AOI I think.</p>
<p>Btw. why does nobody try to shoot the Golem in the head? I'd think they are well prepared and know what they are doing.</p>

							</div>

