					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2026083&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182118" alt="Dr_Grom" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2026083)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;" >Dr_Grom</a></span> <span class="odate time_1531462917 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jul 2018 06:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3871992">
									

<p>&quot;Obskura&quot; sounds Latin. In German the adjective is &quot;obskur&quot;, the noun is &quot;Obskurität&quot;. Though its meaning as occult and dark mystic is not wrong it also means shady, treacherous and such. I think &quot;obscure&quot; in English only means occult and dark mystic etc, right?<br />
I think it perfectly fits in English. I mean, everybody knows from the name alone that it probably is something occult and paramilitary.<br />
But at least to me it sounds weird in German. Naming a black-mages-GOI something occult is fitting, but calling an SS unit something related to criminals? Also the latinish &quot;a&quot; after Obskur doesn't want to fit the Nazi-theme for me.<br />
Especially the SS favored German or pseudo-germanic terms. Some completely made up, sometimes names of VIP, e.g. the units leader, or locations. The OK's director was this Dr. Weiss, right? So it could have been named &quot;Gruppe Weiss&quot; or &quot;Korps Weiss&quot; if you want to use &quot;Korps&quot;. Also some other projects where codenamed. A defensive bio-weapon research group was called &quot;Blitzableiter&quot; (lightning-rod) as it started with &quot;b&quot;. So any German noun starting with &quot;o&quot; would go as a codename for something occult.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>I rarely check forums for updates, so please send PM if you want to talk to me</p>

